import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='adjclose', data=data, label='Adjusted Close')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the stock prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close Price')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='volume', bins=50, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['volume'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Daily Trading Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='date', y='high', ax=ax, label='High', color='green')
    sns.lineplot(data=data, x='date', y='low', ax=ax, label='Low', color='red')

    max_high = data['high'].max()
    min_low = data['low'].min()

    ax.axhline(max_high, linestyle='--', color='green', label=f'Highest: {max_high:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(min_low, linestyle='--', color='red', label=f'Lowest: {min_low:.2f}')

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest price of the stock during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daily_return'] = data['adjclose'].pct_change()
    data['average_daily_return'] = np.mean(data['daily_return'])

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='daily_return', data=data, label='Daily Return')
    plt.axhline(y=data['average_daily_return'].iloc[0], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Daily Return: {data['average_daily_return'].iloc[0]:.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Daily Return')
    plt.title('What is the average daily return of the stock?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
